items.text:
Hey friends and creatives! 

I wanted to share a quick update‚ÄîI'm diving back into the world of **live theater, commercials, movies, and modeling gigs,** and I‚Äôm super excited to reconnect with this passion!

If you or anyone you know has a project or opportunity where you think I‚Äôd be a good fit, **please reach out!** Whether it‚Äôs on stage, in front of the camera, or something creative that needs a fresh face, I‚Äôd love to collaborate and bring my energy to your team.

Here‚Äôs a little about me:

I have experience in theater and acting, plus some modeling under my belt. I‚Äôm ready and eager to jump into new roles and creative projects.

Feel free to message me anytime or tag someone who might be interested!

Thank you all for the support‚Äîit means the world!

This is for an up-and coming rapper signed to Atlantic Records it‚Äôs strictly volunteer of course you get credit and get fed as well as exposure to industry professionals during the premiere. 

Please share and have them email me for more details Janasia99@yahoo.com

items.text: I am new here and and thought I would introduce myself. I am a filmmaker living on the space coast. Not right now, but I might eventually make a casting call, for a short film. I have my eye of a few film festivals. I have made short films before, but it has been a while since I have worked with people. This also wont include payment. It will be for experience and building resume. I might be a bit rusty so it will also be to re-invoke the skills I retain, get back what I have lost, and learn some new ones. It shall be an experience for the both of us. I do a lot of horror so I will be looking for some young scream queens looking to get their foot in the door,  get some experience, and build their resume.

Suche f√ºr ein Musikvideo noch eine Mitspielerin.
 
Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Auf Wunsch kann ich dir auch schon ein paar Songausschnitte zeigen :)

items.text:
Most people set goals.
Very few change their identity.

That‚Äôs the difference.

I stopped asking:
‚ùå ‚ÄúHow do I achieve this?‚Äù

And started asking:
‚úÖ ‚ÄúWho is the person that already has this‚Ä¶ and how do they think, act and show up daily?‚Äù

Because goals don‚Äôt change your life.
Identity does.

You don‚Äôt get confident and then go for it.
You become someone who takes action while scared.

You don‚Äôt wait to feel ready.
You become the person who moves before they feel ready.

Every level of your life requires a different version of you.
New habits.
New standards.
New self-talk.

Your results will always match who you believe you are.

So the real question is:
Who do you need to become next?

üëá Start building that person today.

More mindset + acting career tools here:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActorMindset #SuccessMindset #IdentityShift #ActorsLife #ActingCareer #CreativeEntrepreneur #SelfBelief #DisciplineEqualsFreedom #LevelUp #Performers #FilmActor #UKActors #DreamBigWorkHard

message.text:
Most people set goals.
Very few change their identity.

That‚Äôs the difference.

I stopped asking:
‚ùå ‚ÄúHow do I achieve this?‚Äù

And started asking:
‚úÖ ‚ÄúWho is the person that already has this‚Ä¶ and how do they think, act and show up daily?‚Äù

Because goals don‚Äôt change your life.
Identity does.

You don‚Äôt get confident and then go for it.
You become someone who takes action while scared.

You don‚Äôt wait to feel ready.
You become the person who moves before they feel ready.

Every level of your life requires a different version of you.
New habits.
New standards.
New self-talk.

Your results will always match who you believe you are.

So the real question is:
Who do you need to become next?

üëá Start building that person today.

More mindset + acting career tools here:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

items.text:
Talent is common.

Consistency isn‚Äôt.

The actors who move forward aren‚Äôt always the most gifted‚Ä¶
they‚Äôre the ones who show up on the days they don‚Äôt feel like it.

The tired days.
The doubtful days.
The ‚Äúwhat‚Äôs the point?‚Äù days.

That‚Äôs where careers are built.

Not in big moments ‚Äî in small, repeated actions.

Show up. Train. Improve. Repeat.

CASTING CALL ‚Äì PAID LEAD ROLE (SHORT FILM)

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm a film student at the University of Brighton, and I‚Äôm currently casting the lead role in my graduation short film, *Interference*.

William Rayner ‚Äì male, age flexible (playing 45-60)

This is a largely internal role with minimal dialogue. We‚Äôre looking for a grounded, naturalistic performance, subtle, lived-in, and emotionally contained rather than theatrical.

The role involves acting opposite a stop-motion character, which will be added in post-production. On set, stand-ins will be used for eyeline and blocking, and performers will be fully supported throughout the process.

PAY & PRACTICALS:

Paid role (¬£100 per day, 8-hour maximum day with breaks) 

Shoot length: 4‚Äì5 days.

Shoot location: Sussex (Hastings & Lewes).

Dates: Late February / early March (flexible based on your schedule within 21 Feb ‚Äì 29 Mar).

Travel & accommodation fully covered (Airbnb provided).

PRODUCTION INFO:

This is an independent student short film produced as part of my graduation project at the University of Brighton. We plan to submit the finished film to UK and international film festivals.

If this sounds like something you‚Äôd be interested in, feel free to send us an email (interferenceshort@gmail.com), comment or DM, and I‚Äôll send over the full casting package with some more information.

Thanks so much!

Elsie Gregory ‚Äì Writer/Director

Actors Wanted!  - Feb 2nd

We are casting for a short comedy commercial as part of our final year for UWE Bristol Filmmaking BA course. 

This is a student production, seeking voluntary actors. The film is non-commercial and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

Bristol-based, evening shoot on Feb 2nd.

To apply, please send headshots, showreels and CVs to koby2.day@live.uwe.ac.uk

Thanks!

attachments.ocrText: The main content is a casting call for "Wheel or No Wheel", a comedic spoof of classic quiz shows set in Neanderthal Times. The theme involves two contestants, a Scottish Hero, and a gameshow host. The background features a spinning wheel with a blue-lit setting. Text is in yellow and black on a dark background. Objects include a red UWE Bristol logo, wheel graphics, and text boxes.

items.text:
Most people set goals.
Very few change their identity.

That‚Äôs the difference.

I stopped asking:
‚ùå ‚ÄúHow do I achieve this?‚Äù

And started asking:
‚úÖ ‚ÄúWho is the person that already has this‚Ä¶ and how do they think, act and show up daily?‚Äù

Because goals don‚Äôt change your life.
Identity does.

You don‚Äôt get confident and then go for it.
You become someone who takes action while scared.

You don‚Äôt wait to feel ready.
You become the person who moves before they feel ready.

Every level of your life requires a different version of you.
New habits.
New standards.
New self-talk.

Your results will always match who you believe you are.

So the real question is:
Who do you need to become next?

üëá Start building that person today.

More mindset + acting career tools here:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActorMindset #SuccessMindset #IdentityShift #ActorsLife #ActingCareer #CreativeEntrepreneur #SelfBelief #DisciplineEqualsFreedom #LevelUp #Performers #FilmActor #UKActors #DreamBigWorkHard

## **MAJOR AWard WINNING PODCAST BOOKING REAL PEOPLE: **

We are currently casting for a major multi-award-winning podcast focused on mental health and personal growth. While our show frequently features interviews with experts, we are now seeking everyday people to share stories that our listeners can deeply identify with.

Specifically looking for couples (28 and older, nationwide) who have dealt with infidelity, whether you have stayed together or have since broken up. We are interested in hearing how you Both navigated this issue & if you are Both open to sharing your journey with our audience and this award winning host.

Participants must be willing to be open and vulnerable about their experiences. Travel/Compensation is provided for those selected to appear. Both Partners must be willing to participate to be a part of the process.

This is a Nationwide Casting Call. All Races. All Sexes. All Sexualities. All Religious backgrounds. We are however searching for traditional styles of marriage.

We would love to have you join us: Please feel free to apply at either link.

CASTING CALL for a Short film *RYLIE* 
A Dramatic Sci/Fi short film about a couple through Grief and the Afterlife, funded by the Toronto Arts Council. Paid. Meals included. 

Non-Union

Shooting In Mid-May in Toronto, ON, Canada.

LOGLINE: Glitches in her old footage drag a grieving woman back through the stages of loss, forcing her to confront the remnants of a relationship she can‚Äôt release and the growing gaps in her own story. 

**DAVID: SUPPORTING**

Late 20s / early 30s. Stylish but unshowy. Quiet confidence. A lived-in edge.  Creative, sensitive, observant. Carries traces of a past life: recovery, scars, depth.

Once deeply connected to RYLIE before his tragic accident. Appears both as her boyfriend and as a ghost ‚Äî intimate, restrained, emotionally present rather than overtly ‚Äúspooky.‚Äù

A modern romantic with a subtle punk ethos (attitude, not costume). (2 full days) $250/day

**ROOMMATE: SUPPORTING**

Early‚Äìmid 20s. Social, independent, and perpetually in motion.  juggling plans, group chats. Loves a bit of gossip and the comfort of communal chaos.

Frequently misses the quieter emotional beats in the room, not out of insensitivity but because she assumes everything will sort itself out. Brings warmth, momentum, and gentle comic relief to RYLIE‚Äôs interior world. (1 day) $250/day

**3 TRENDY FRIENDS: 2 FEATURED EXTRAS +1 BIT PART**

18 to mid 20s. all ethnicities / any genders. Three close friends, think subcultures: ravers, bandmates, skaters, goths with 2yk style. A small speaking role will be for one of the friends. Please submit separately or as a group if you can. Individual submissions will be accepted as well. Pay is based on 1 hr of shooting. $100 per person plus meal. Estimated commitment is 3-4 hours.

Please submit self-tapes via Backstage, Actors Access, or through ryliecasting@gmail.com, and please share with anyone who might be interested. thanks!

https://www.backstage.com/casting/rylie-a-scifi-drama-funded-by-tac-3072572/

FINAL CASTING CALL!
COMIC CON DOCUMENTARY | CASTING CALL 

Hello,

I am currently on my BA Hons Degree in Media Production at South Gloucestershire and Stroud College. 

I am doing a 6 - minute documentary that uses a core participants to explore how Cosplay is not a performance but entertainment, a way identity is expressed, shaped and performed.

It will document the participants' experience and highlight the experience from a first - time attendees, offering both a personal insight and broader perspective of UK Comic Con Culture. 

I need someone to Cosplay Catwoman aged 18 - 40 at Bristol Comic Con on the 8th March 2026 at Ashton Gate Stadium. 

There will also be an interview segment following the event.

Please let me know if you'd be interested?

I will pay for your ticket too, it's from 10:30am - 16:00pm

I'd pay you ¬£200.00

It's for my BA Hons Degree FMP and determines if I pass or fail.

items.text:
CASTING CALL

We are looking for 2 children and 4 adults for a period piece (1980's) short film set in the Richmond area. Our story is about how two childhood friends' lives and worlds are affected by immigration laws. Below are the character descriptions for each role.

ADELINA (White, 8-11 to play age eight
Daughter of Bulgarian immigrants. Imaginative, bold, and instantly drawn to Marvin. She moves through the world with curiosity and a quiet confidence that makes her easy to root for.

MARVIN (Black, 8-11 to play age eight
Son of a Black convenience store owner. Quiet, creative, and thoughtful. He loves playing pretend and dress-up and has a sensitivity and wisdom well beyond his age. MUST BE COMFORTABLE PLAYING DRESS UP AND WEARING FACE PAINT.

RICHARD (Black, 35-40)
Marvin‚Äôs father and the owner of the neighborhood convenience store. Warm, generous, and deeply community-minded. Best friends with Petar and unafraid to help him, even when it means paying him under the table.

PETAR (White, 35-40)
Adelina‚Äôs father and a Bulgarian immigrant. Protective, loyal, and soft-spoken. He carries the stress of providing for his family with a quiet determination.

YANA (White, 35-40)
Adelina‚Äôs mother and a Bulgarian immigrant. Caring, practical, and firm when she needs to be. She is the steady force that keeps her family grounded.

POLICEMAN (White, 32-38)
A no-nonsense officer whose internalized racism shows through in subtle but unmistakable ways during his interactions with Richard and Petar. He represents the tension and fear the families navigate in their daily lives.

PRODUCTION DATES: March 7th, 8th, 14th, and 15th

LOCATION: Richmond VA

NON UNION

PAID ROLE

SUBMISSION PROCESS:

CASTING CALL

We are looking for 2 children and 4 adults for a period piece (1980's) short film set in the Richmond area. Our story is about how two childhood friends' lives and worlds are affected by immigration laws. Below are the character descriptions for each role.

ADELINA (White, 8-11 to play age eight
Daughter of Bulgarian immigrants. Imaginative, bold, and instantly drawn to Marvin. She moves through the world with curiosity and a quiet confidence that makes her easy to root for.

MARVIN (Black, 8-11 to play age eight
Son of a Black convenience store owner. Quiet, creative, and thoughtful. He loves playing pretend and dress-up and has a sensitivity and wisdom well beyond his age. MUST BE COMFORTABLE PLAYING DRESS UP AND WEARING FACE PAINT.

RICHARD (Black, 35-40)
Marvin‚Äôs father and the owner of the neighborhood convenience store. Warm, generous, and deeply community-minded. Best friends with Petar and unafraid to help him, even when it means paying him under the table.

PETAR (White, 35-40)
Adelina‚Äôs father and a Bulgarian immigrant. Protective, loyal, and soft-spoken. He carries the stress of providing for his family with a quiet determination.

YANA (White, 35-40)
Adelina‚Äôs mother and a Bulgarian immigrant. Caring, practical, and firm when she needs to be. She is the steady force that keeps her family grounded.

POLICEMAN (White, 32-38)
A no-nonsense officer whose internalized racism shows through in subtle but unmistakable ways during his interactions with Richard and Petar. He represents the tension and fear the families navigate in their daily lives.

PRODUCTION DATES: March 7th, 8th, 14th, and 15th

LOCATION: Richmond VA

üçí **CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)**

***CHERRY ON TOP***** ‚Äî Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements**

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 ‚Äì March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh‚Äôs wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Catherine‚Äôs husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed‚Äîuntil his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Alec‚Äôs wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy‚Äîespecially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! üçí

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

As we move forward with Hocus Pocus: The Mini-Series, we continue adding new elements to the story ‚Äî new cast members, new locations, and everything in between.

Winifred, Sarah, and Mary are truly trying to wipe out the entire town‚Ä¶ one person at a time.

items.text:
Most people set goals.
Very few change their identity.

That‚Äôs the difference.

I stopped asking:
‚ùå ‚ÄúHow do I achieve this?‚Äù

And started asking:
‚úÖ ‚ÄúWho is the person that already has this‚Ä¶ and how do they think, act and show up daily?‚Äù

Because goals don‚Äôt change your life.
Identity does.

You don‚Äôt get confident and then go for it.
You become someone who takes action while scared.

You don‚Äôt wait to feel ready.
You become the person who moves before they feel ready.

Every level of your life requires a different version of you.
New habits.
New standards.
New self-talk.

Your results will always match who you believe you are.

So the real question is:
Who do you need to become next?

üëá Start building that person today.

More mindset + acting career tools here:

message.text:
Nothing Human Is Alien To Us
 
‚ÄúWe all bear within us the potentiality for every kind of passion, every fate, every way of life.  Nothing human is alien to us.  If this were not so, we could not understand other people, either in life or in art.  But inheritance and upbringing foster individual experiences and develop only a few of our thousands of possibilities.  The others gradually sicken and die.‚Äù
- Max Reinhardt, ‚ÄúThe Actor,‚Äù Actors on Acting

NEW YEAR, NEW CLASS!!! 

Let‚Äôs explore the depth, boundaries, authenticity and grow the range of your acting. 

START THE YEAR INSPIRED! 

NOW is the perfect time to sign up for all or any of the 3 steps our comprehensive CERTIFICATE PROGRAM! 

STEP 1: PRIVATE COACHING - 

6x1hr sessions, learn or re-enforce the essentials, with trusted process preparation techniques and direction, we prepare and tape contrasting monologues. Add to your reel!

STEP 2: SEMIPRIVATE, SCENE-STUDY: 
3x2hr sessions. I partner you, we review and apply the preparation techniques. We tape 2 scenes with playback, notes and direction, with a focus on on-camera technique - living in the scene! Add to your reel! 
 
Or .. alternate STEP 2:  SIGN UP FOR THE JANUARY THURSDAY NIGHT SCENE-STUDY CLASS: 
Feb. 5, 12, 19, 26: 6-9 pm. 

We‚Äôre preparing and taping scenes, telling compelling stories, applying foundational, analytical preparation techniques, with a focus on screen acting skills, using 2 cameras. 

STEP 3: THE SUCCESSFUL AUDITIONS WORKSHOP:
2 days, sharpen your audition skills, plus SELF-TAPE AUDITIONS, for commercials and film and TV series, we tape your 2 auditions, with critique, coaching, direction and demonstration. Next: FEB. 22nd & 23rd, repeats every 3rd mth. 

CERTIFICATE PROGRAM (ALL 3 STEPS):
Comprehensive training! 

Add tape for your reel! Agent referrals! For prices and more information:
416 294-3754 / bongoproductions.com

sharedPost.text:
CASTING CALL

Title: Where He Is
Format: Narrative Short / Proof of Concept
Genre: Drama
Union Status: Non-Union
Shoot Location: TBD (Small-town / suburban) - Likely Louisville, KY and/or Owensboro, KY
Shoot Dates: TBD - Late Summer/Early Fall 2026
Compensation: Paid (TBD) + meals + copy + festival exposure

Please note: DMs will be ignored. Please follow the submission instructions at the end of this post. 

LOGLINE

After the sudden death of a fellow Navy veteran, a grieving husband and father begins to quietly unravel as his faith collides with loss, hypocrisy, and unanswered questions, forcing him to confront what belief means when certainty is gone.

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Where He Is is a restrained, character-driven drama exploring grief, doubt, and faith without easy answers. Told through intimate conversations and moments of silence, the film follows a Navy veteran navigating loss while trying to remain present for his family, even as the beliefs that once grounded him begin to slip.

This is a proof-of-concept short, designed to showcase performance, tone, and emotional depth rather than spectacle. The film prioritizes realism, subtlety, and lived-in performances. Loosely based on the writers real life experiences. 

ROLES AVAILABLE - (Character Names Subject to Change)

MARK (Lead) - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

A Navy veteran, husband, and father. Mark is disciplined, functional, and emotionally guarded. Someone who knows how to keep moving even when he‚Äôs breaking inside. He is not angry at God so much as disoriented by the people who claim to speak for Him.

This role requires an actor comfortable with internalized performance, minimal dialogue, and emotional restraint. Much of Mark‚Äôs journey is conveyed through silence, posture, and small behavioral shifts.

Key traits: Grounded, observant, quietly conflicted. Carries grief without theatrics. Faithful in action, doubtful in belief.

SARAH - Female | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

Mark‚Äôs wife. Steady, compassionate, and emotionally perceptive, but not immune to doubt herself. Sarah believes, but her faith is not performative or unshakable. She is trying to support her husband while privately confronting her own uncertainty.

This role requires emotional transparency without melodrama. Sarah is not a moral counterweight, she is a partner, equally vulnerable.

Key traits: Warm but honest, Emotionally resilient, not naive. Comfortable with silence and subtle shifts.

PREACHER - Male | 55‚Äì70 | Any ethnicity

A longtime pastor who speaks gently and without ego. He is thoughtful, self-aware, and willing to admit failure. He does not offer answers, only honesty. This character should feel like someone who has lived through regret, not someone performing wisdom.

This role benefits from an actor who can convey gravitas through stillness and allow uncertainty to live in the pauses.

Key traits: Calm, reflective, humble. Comfortable admitting ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know‚Äù. Authority without control.

DAVID - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity (Day Player)

A fellow Navy veteran and close friend of the deceased. David is sincere, grounded, and emotionally open in a way Mark isn‚Äôt, yet. He represents belief as survival rather than doctrine.

Key traits: Quiet strength, Emotionally accessible, Deep sense of brotherhood.

KIDS (2 roles)

Any gender | Ages 6‚Äì9 | Any ethnicity

Mark and Sarah‚Äôs children. Natural, curious, and emotionally perceptive. These roles are small but important, innocent questions carry heavy weight.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:

Actors interested in submitting should email: skaldsagastudios@gmail.com

Subject Line: Where He Is ‚Äì [Role] ‚Äì [Actor‚Äôs Name]

Please include: Resume, Headshots, Demo reel (if available)

Submission Deadline: Friday, February 13th @ 10:00 PM EST

Selected actors will be contacted with audition details.

items.text:
Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - Non-union **

Looking for Slavic/Eastern European looking actors for small, non-speaking roles in short film, During Winter, I Thought of My Father, a Russian language short film by Daniil Vasilyev. 

**ACTORS DO NOT NEED TO SPEAK RUSSIAN AS THE ROLES ARE NON-SPEAKING. **

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

items.text:
SHORT FILM CASTING CALL: See You At The Funktion

Genre: Comedy/Coming of Age/Drama

LOGLINE:

A UK-based young Hungarian woman struggles to reveal that she‚Äôs moving abroad at her grandpa‚Äôs disco-themed 70th birthday party.

**Roles are voluntary, but meals and travel expenses will be covered.**

We are a University of Westminster Final Year Film Production, so we would love to hire **London-based actors.**

**Shooting Mid-Late Feb/Early March in NW London**

**PLEASE CONTACT W1990635@WESTMINSTER.AC.UK OR CAITLYN.MADELEY101@GMAIL.COM IF INTERESTED IN ANY ROLES.**

Looking to fill the following roles; some require **Hungarian** Language fluency.

**DALIA (HUNGARIAN LANGUAGE NEEDED) PLAYING AGE 20 - 30 - LEAD - FEMALE**

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

*Lead Roles for Interactive Game + Vertical Drama Production*

**Project: **The Fame Game 2: L.A. Heartbreaker

**Production: **Snail Games / Interactive Films

**Location: **Los Angeles, CA

**Shoot Dates: **March 2026 (approx. 20 days)

**Rate: **$500‚Äì$800/day

**ABOUT THE PROJECT**

This is an interactive video game production combining romance, comedy, and drama with multiple branching storylines and endings. The project involves extensive ensemble work, romantic/comedic chemistry across multiple pairings, and emotionally complex character arcs. Open to all ethnicities except where noted. Acting experience is not required, and active social media presence is a plus.

**AUDITION PROCESS**

**Round 1: **Virtual Interview (unpaid)

**Round 2: **In-person audition in Los Angeles ($100/30 min, paid) or self-tape if unable to travel

**Talent invited to round 2 must:**
* Participate in an online voting campaign
* Sign release and waiver allowing use of audition materials for voting and promotional purposes

**MIA ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Open

Gentle and competent mentor with a cool, wild streak. Professional exterior that gradually reveals a shy, jealous romantic side through interactions with the male lead.

**Requirements:**
* Sophisticated demeanor; ability to convey subtle emotional shifts
* Stunt/action experience a plus (driving scenes)

**CAMILLE ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 24 | Ethnicity: Open

A confident, bold print model who plays games with love but transforms into someone capable of genuine emotion. Sexy, fiery, and provocative, but ultimately vulnerable.

**Requirements:**
* Model experience a plus
* Comfortable with flirtatious/sensual scenes
* Strong emotional range

**LIN MUYUN ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 27 | Ethnicity: Mixed / Half Asian

Gentle and elegant on the surface, highly possessive underneath. Carries childhood trauma and develops complicated feelings for her stepbrother. Borderline obsessive but deeply sympathetic.

**Requirements:**
* Comfortable with intimate/intense emotional scenes
* Ability to portray psychological complexity

**ROLES**
**SHUHAN HO ‚Äî Male Lead**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

An ordinary international student mistaken for a wealthy heir with an identical appearance. Vain and drawn to glamour, but kind-hearted beneath the surface. Awkward yet sincere, constantly juggling multiple romantic entanglements while navigating his double identity.

**Requirements:**
* Strong comedic timing; ability to portray vulnerability and growth
* Chemistry with multiple female leads
* Must play two characters (Shuhan Ho and Shuhan ‚ÄúRichie‚Äù Ho)
* Mandarin Chinese fluency required

**SHUHAN ‚ÄúRICHIE‚Äù HO ‚Äî Male Supporting**

Age: 23 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

The true rich heir‚Äîand a complete emotional predator. Hedonistic, selfish, and unapologetically cruel in matters of love. Free of guilt or conscience, he is the protagonist's dark mirror and the original source of the story's turmoil.

**Requirements: **Same as Shuhan Ho (dual role)

**SUSANNA ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 21 | Ethnicity: East Asian

A pampered rich heiress, innocent and stubborn, completely clueless about everyday life. Outwardly confident but inwardly fragile and insecure. Clumsy yet endearing in her attempts to win love.

**Requirements:**
* Ability to balance comedy with emotional vulnerability
* Physical comedy skills preferred
* Must deliver Chinese, Japanese, or Korean dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation (fluency not required)

**LI SISI ‚Äî Female Lead**

Age: 22 | Ethnicity: Chinese / East Asian

Pure, kind, girl-next-door type. The male lead's moral compass and childhood sweetheart. Sweet but capable of jealousy and testing born from insecurity.

**Requirements:**
* Natural, understated performance style
* Chemistry with male lead; ability to convey heartbreak
* Must deliver Chinese dialogue with authentic/native pronunciation

**TO SUBMIT**
1. Headshot and full-body photo
2. Acting resume

**Send submissions to: **casting@rarefloweragency.com

**Deadline: Feb 8, 2026 (12PM, PST)**

CASTING CALL

Title: Where He Is
Format: Narrative Short / Proof of Concept
Genre: Drama
Union Status: Non-Union
Shoot Location: TBD (Small-town / suburban) - Likely Louisville, KY and/or Owensboro, KY
Shoot Dates: TBD - Late Summer/Early Fall 2026
Compensation: Paid (TBD) + meals + copy + festival exposure

Please note: DMs will be ignored. Please follow the submission instructions at the end of this post. 

LOGLINE

After the sudden death of a fellow Navy veteran, a grieving husband and father begins to quietly unravel as his faith collides with loss, hypocrisy, and unanswered questions, forcing him to confront what belief means when certainty is gone.

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Where He Is is a restrained, character-driven drama exploring grief, doubt, and faith without easy answers. Told through intimate conversations and moments of silence, the film follows a Navy veteran navigating loss while trying to remain present for his family, even as the beliefs that once grounded him begin to slip.

This is a proof-of-concept short, designed to showcase performance, tone, and emotional depth rather than spectacle. The film prioritizes realism, subtlety, and lived-in performances. Loosely based on the writers real life experiences. 

ROLES AVAILABLE - (Character Names Subject to Change)

MARK (Lead) - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

A Navy veteran, husband, and father. Mark is disciplined, functional, and emotionally guarded. Someone who knows how to keep moving even when he‚Äôs breaking inside. He is not angry at God so much as disoriented by the people who claim to speak for Him.

This role requires an actor comfortable with internalized performance, minimal dialogue, and emotional restraint. Much of Mark‚Äôs journey is conveyed through silence, posture, and small behavioral shifts.

Key traits: Grounded, observant, quietly conflicted. Carries grief without theatrics. Faithful in action, doubtful in belief.

SARAH - Female | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

Mark‚Äôs wife. Steady, compassionate, and emotionally perceptive, but not immune to doubt herself. Sarah believes, but her faith is not performative or unshakable. She is trying to support her husband while privately confronting her own uncertainty.

This role requires emotional transparency without melodrama. Sarah is not a moral counterweight, she is a partner, equally vulnerable.

Key traits: Warm but honest, Emotionally resilient, not naive. Comfortable with silence and subtle shifts.

PREACHER - Male | 55‚Äì70 | Any ethnicity

A longtime pastor who speaks gently and without ego. He is thoughtful, self-aware, and willing to admit failure. He does not offer answers, only honesty. This character should feel like someone who has lived through regret, not someone performing wisdom.

This role benefits from an actor who can convey gravitas through stillness and allow uncertainty to live in the pauses.

Key traits: Calm, reflective, humble. Comfortable admitting ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know‚Äù. Authority without control.

DAVID - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity (Day Player)

A fellow Navy veteran and close friend of the deceased. David is sincere, grounded, and emotionally open in a way Mark isn‚Äôt, yet. He represents belief as survival rather than doctrine.

Key traits: Quiet strength, Emotionally accessible, Deep sense of brotherhood.

KIDS (2 roles)

Any gender | Ages 6‚Äì9 | Any ethnicity

Mark and Sarah‚Äôs children. Natural, curious, and emotionally perceptive. These roles are small but important, innocent questions carry heavy weight.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:

Actors interested in submitting should email: skaldsagastudios@gmail.com

Subject Line: Where He Is ‚Äì [Role] ‚Äì [Actor‚Äôs Name]

Please include: Resume, Headshots, Demo reel (if available)

Submission Deadline: Friday, February 13th @ 10:00 PM EST

Selected actors will be contacted with audition details.

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/5hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form

FINAL CASTING CALL!
COMIC CON DOCUMENTARY | CASTING CALL 

Hello,

I am currently on my BA Hons Degree in Media Production at South Gloucestershire and Stroud College. 

I am doing a 6 - minute documentary that uses a core participants to explore how Cosplay is not a performance but entertainment, a way identity is expressed, shaped and performed.

It will document the participants' experience and highlight the experience from a first - time attendees, offering both a personal insight and broader perspective of UK Comic Con Culture. 

I need someone to Cosplay Catwoman aged 18 - 40 at Bristol Comic Con on the 8th March 2026 at Ashton Gate Stadium. 

There will also be an interview segment following the event.

Please let me know if you'd be interested?

I will pay for your ticket too, it's from 10:30am - 16:00pm

I'd pay you ¬£200.00

It's for my BA Hons Degree FMP and determines if I pass or fail.

items.text:
Held - A Short Film by Jake Nova. üé•
Sometimes what we hold onto, holds us back. ü•Ä

üé¨ Excited to share my project; a short film Held by myself. The story explores enotional containment and masking emotions ‚Äî a theme that resonated with me and one I believe needs to be shared more.

This was a self-tape project I created as part of building my portfolio, and I‚Äôm proud of the professional approach and care that went into it. Although recorded in a few takes and slightly rushed due to environment I‚Äôm currently living in, I am always practicing and expanding my skills to excel in this career.

I‚Äôm Always looking to grow and connect with representation and collaborators who are looking for talent üé≠

items.text:
üé•Casting Call: Liverpool Institute of Performing Arts (LIPA) First Year Short Film 
This is a non-paid short film. 

‚ÄòGood Company‚Äô - A surreal blend of Sitcom and Psychological Horror. 

Shooting in Liverpool between April and March, dates are TBC. 

Good Company is a short film that blurs the lines between fiction and reality exploring themes of surrealism, analog horror and unreliable reality. 

After starting a new tenancy, Tommy tries to conform to the eccentrics of his new friend group but when cracks start to form in his everyday life, he is left battling with reality and surfacing memories of his past. 

We are searching for 5 people to play Tommy, Lulu, Albert, Nicole or The Director. Must be able to do an American accent. 

This is a first year non-paid LIPA production. The film may be submitted to festivals and will be shown within LIPA. Open to Liverpool-based actors or those who are able to self-travel. 

If you are interested please DM or email:

h.haynes24@lipa.ac.uk

Or use the link below to book an audition time:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfklny6WooIdaYP54DVvxJ2Kl7MTW-vzWGiqe6O15rPhQx9gg/viewform?usp=header

If emailing, please include a showreel (if available) and the role you are applying for. A segment of the script will then be emailed back to you for a teams meeting audition. 

Auditions are held between the 2nd and 4th of February from 6pm to 8pm. If you are unable to do these dates, we can arrange a different time.

items.summary:
üé•Casting Call: Liverpool Institute of Performing Arts (LIPA) First Year Short Film 
This is a non-paid short film. 

‚ÄòGood Company‚Äô - A surreal blend of Sitcom and Psychological Horror. 

Shooting in Liverpool between April and March, dates are TBC. 

Good Company is a short film that blurs the lines between fiction and reality exploring themes of surrealism, analog horror and unreliable reality. 

After starting a new tenancy, Tommy tries to conform to the eccentrics of his new friend group but when cracks start to form in his everyday life, he is left battling with reality and surfacing memories of his past. 

We are searching for 5 people to play Tommy, Lulu, Albert, Nicole or The Director. Must be able to do an American accent. 

This is a first year non-paid LIPA production. The film may be submitted to festivals and will be shown within LIPA. Open to Liverpool-based actors or those who are able to self-travel. 

If you are interested please DM or email:

h.haynes24@lipa.ac.uk

Or use the link below to book an audition time:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfklny6WooIdaYP54DVvxJ2Kl7MTW-vzWGiqe6O15rPhQx9gg/viewform?usp=header

If emailing, please include a showreel (if available) and the role you are applying for. A segment of the script will then be emailed back to you for a teams meeting audition. 

Auditions are held between the 2nd and 4th of February from 6pm to 8pm. If you are unable to do these dates, we can arrange a different time.

**Casting call ‚Äì Male (35‚Äì50) ‚Äì Paid ‚Äì Merseyside / Manchester / Liverpool**

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Angelo, founder of **Knapios**, a UK clothing brand focused on **timeless design and natural materials**.

Our **first product is a men‚Äôs polo shirt**, and for this initial campaign I‚Äôm looking to photograph **one male (35‚Äì50)** for an **elegant, natural lifestyle shoot in a studio setting**.

This is **not a runway or influencer shoot** ‚Äî we‚Äôre looking for a **classic, authentic, real presence**.
The shoot will be calm and simple (standing, walking, natural posture ‚Äî nothing overly posed).

**Details:**
‚Ä¢ Location: Merseyside / Manchester / Liverpool
‚Ä¢ Setting: studio
‚Ä¢ Duration: approx. 1‚Äì2 hours
‚Ä¢ Paid
‚Ä¢ Modelling experience not required

If you‚Äôre interested (or know someone who would suit), please comment or DM with a couple of recent photos.

Thank you!

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
‚Ä¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"

‚Ä¢ Type: Short

‚Ä¢ Location: Boulder, CO, Denver, CO

‚Ä¢ Compensation: $25/day (negotiable), lunch provided

‚Ä¢ Shooting Dates: Sunday, January 25th & Sunday, February 1st

SYNOPSIS

Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband, Benny, by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ Benny D'Angelo: Male, 23-35
Vivian's husband. A well-off businessman who fell in love easily, only to now find that his wife might have married him just for the money.

‚Ä¢ Officer K: Male, 30+
A no-nonsense cop with a keen attention to detail. He arrives on the scene of an apparent drug bust, only to discover there may be something much more sinister at hand.
(Only needed on 1/25)

TO SUBMIT:

‚Ä¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition (please submit by Friday, January 23)

‚Ä¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush"

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 m√§nnliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 m√§nnliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht‚Äôs im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Bank√ºberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe m√ºssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme l√∂st.

sharedPost.text:
Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We‚Äôre approaching our first deadline of the season, and we‚Äôre officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone ‚Äî and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog ‚Äî whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

message.text:
Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video ‚ÄúCITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words‚Äù captures the festival‚Äôs spirit and philosophy ‚Äì highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival‚Äôs film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

üîó Learn more & apply: https://iff.cittador.com

#cittadorfilmfestival #indiefilmfest #independentfilm #ciffvienna
